  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced", 
    "date": "2003-07-22", 
    "text": "Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) make permanent provisions allowing the expensing of environmental remediation costs; (2) revise the definition of \"qualified contaminated site\" to include toxic as well as hazardous substances; (3) include within the definition of \"hazardous or toxic substances\" extremely hazardous substances, as defined by Federal law, and petroleum contaminants; and (4) eliminate the recapture of the expensing deduction upon the sale of environmental remediation property."
